cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

This paper involves video prediction and weather forecasting, which are both related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel loss function and utilizes group normalization, which are related to machine learning techniques, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a neural network, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves weather forecasting, which may involve information retrieval techniques, suggesting that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
